abstract: The Sanders online army resembles President Trump’s most ardent supporters in more ways than either side might care to admit.
snippet: The Sanders online army resembles President Trump’s most ardent supporters in more ways than either side might care to admit.
lead_paragraph: Barbara Boxer minces no words when it comes to describing the people usually known as the Bernie Bros — a subset of Bernie Sanders supporters who hope to take over the Democratic Party and remake it in their image.

headline_main: Once Skeptical, Senate Republicans Are All In on Trump
headline_print_headline: A Party Now Less Likely To Tell Trump ‘Enough’

abstract: The narrow vote came after Republican senators said they did not need to hear more evidence, and pressed toward acquitting President Trump next week.
snippet: The narrow vote came after Republican senators said they did not need to hear more evidence, and pressed toward acquitting President Trump next week.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Senate brought President Trump to the brink of acquittal on Friday of charges that he abused his power and obstructed Congress, as Republicans voted to block consideration of new witnesses and documents in his impeachment trial and shut down a final push by Democrats to bolster their case for the president’s removal.

snippet: On a July 25 telephone call with the president of Ukraine, President Trump described Ambassador Yovanovitch as “bad news” and said, ominously, “She’s going to go through some things.”
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The American ambassador whose abrupt recall from Ukraine helped lead to President Trump’s impeachment has retired from the State Department, a person familiar with her plans confirmed on Friday.

headline_main: The Impeachment Trial Nears a Finale
headline_print_headline: The Impeachment Trial Nears a Finale

abstract: Several Senate Republicans said that even if President Trump did everything impeachment managers said, he should not be removed.
snippet: Several Senate Republicans said that even if President Trump did everything impeachment managers said, he should not be removed.
lead_paragraph: The Senate voted on Friday nearly along party lines to block additional witnesses and evidence in President Trump’s impeachment trial, effectively accelerating the proceedings toward a final vote, which is expected to be held Wednesday.

abstract: Britain exits Europe. It will be poorer, above all in its shriveled heart.
snippet: Britain exits Europe. It will be poorer, above all in its shriveled heart.
lead_paragraph: I have covered many stories that marked me over the past 40 years, in war zones and outside them, but none that has affected me as personally as Britain’s exit from the European Union. Brexit Day, now upon us, feels like the end of hope, a moral collapse, a self-amputation that will make the country where I grew up poorer in every sense.

abstract: As he discussed the possibility of a White House meeting for Ukraine’s president, President Trump’s lawyer asked to save the Kyiv mayor’s job.
snippet: As he discussed the possibility of a White House meeting for Ukraine’s president, President Trump’s lawyer asked to save the Kyiv mayor’s job.
lead_paragraph: KYIV, Ukraine — When Rudolph W. Giuliani met with a top aide to Ukraine’s president last summer, he discussed the prospect of a coveted White House meeting for the president while seeking Ukraine’s commitment to certain investigations that could benefit President Trump politically.

abstract: In a podcast interview on Friday, Mrs. Clinton also described the caucuses in Iowa, where Mr. Sanders leads in some polls, as “undemocratic.”
snippet: In a podcast interview on Friday, Mrs. Clinton also described the caucuses in Iowa, where Mr. Sanders leads in some polls, as “undemocratic.”
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Hillary Clinton said on Friday in a podcast interview that Senator Bernie Sanders and his supporters did not do enough to unify the Democratic Party after the prolonged 2016 primary, calling the behavior of his supporters “distressing” and saying it affected the general election.
